[{"id":"VH991761","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH866000.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The syntax in line 27 (“Expir’d . . . To-morrow”) emphasizes the speaker’s sense of the</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH991761_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><p class=\"lead_in\"><span class=\"compose_cluster_phrase type:ordinal\"></span>  Read the following poem carefully before you choose your answers.</p><p class=\"introduction passage-intro\">This poem was written in 1714, soon after the author, an Anglo-Irish satirist, moved from England to Ireland.</p><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"poetry style:1\"><div class=\"title\"><p class=\"title_line passage-title\">In Sickness</p></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>’Tis true—then why should I repine,<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">1</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">complain</span></span></span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>To see my Life so fast decline?</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>But, why obscurely here alone?</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Where I am neither lov’d nor known.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">5</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>My State of Health none care to learn;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>My Life is here no Soul’s Concern.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And, those with whom I now converse,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Without a Tear will tend my Herse.<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">2</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">hearse</span></span></span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Remov’d from kind <span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">Arbuthnot</span>’s<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">3</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">John Arbuthnot (1667–1735), Scottish physician</span></span> Aid,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">10</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Who knows his Art but not the Trade;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Preferring his Regard for me</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Before his Credit or his Fee.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Some formal Visits, Looks, and Words,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>What meer Humanity affords,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">15</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>I meet perhaps from three or four,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>From whom I once expected more;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Which those who tend the Sick for pay</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Can act as decently as they.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>But no obliging, tender Friend</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">20</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>To help at my approaching End,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>My Life is now a Burthen grown</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>To others, e’er it be my own.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Y<span class=\"formatted_text font_variant:small-caps\">E</span> formal Weepers for the Sick,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>In your last Offices be quick:</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">25</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And spare my absent Friends the Grief</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>To hear, yet give me no Relief;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Expir’d To-day, entomb’d To-morrow,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>When known, will save a double Sorrow.</span><br/></div><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\"></span></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">poignancy of loss</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">indifference of others</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">brevity of friendship</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">solitude of death</p>"],"answer":2}]